Three cars were set alight during clashes in Sandton last week. JOHANNESBURG - Tourism Minister Tokozile Xasa has slammed ongoing violence between metered taxi and Uber drivers.Three cars were set alight during clashes in Sandton last week.Xasa's office fears the long-standing dispute between metered taxi operators and Uber could impact tourism.The minister's spokesperson Mahlodi Muofhe shared the concerns. Tourists have a wide choice of destinations. The minister is doing her best to attract tourists to grow our economy. WATCH: Vehicles torched as Uber operators, metered taxis drivers clash(Edited by Shimoney Regter)